===Etymology===
From their primary residence in [[Pennsylvania]] and from {{bor|en|pfl|Deitsch||[[German]]}}, their own [[endonym]], gradually modified under influence from {{m|en|Dutch}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|Pennsylvania Dutch}}

# {{lb|en|plural}} Those people of [[German]] origin who settled in the Pennsylvania area prior to 1800, and their descendants.
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Their [[language]], [[Pennsylvania German]], a [[High German]] language descended from [[Palatine German]].
# {{lb|en|nonstandard}} The Old Order [[Amish]].

